{{spoiler}} {{Infobox Character |name = E |image = e (xenoblade).png |species = [[Moebius]] |age = |gender = Male |haircolor = |eyecolor = |affiliation = [[Consul]]s |voiceactorjp = |voiceactoreng = |appearances = {{XC3}} }} '''Consul E''' is a character in {{XC3}}.
== Overview == E is the [[Consul]] of [[Colony Iota]].
== Story == At some point prior to the story, E was assigned to a [[Keves]]i [[Colony]] that fought against [[Colony Delta]], only to abandon the colony. He was later assigned to Colony Iota, knowing that [[Alexandria]] conspired to assassinate the previous commander, but did not do anything to stop it, though he informs [[Q]] about this. E is seen at [[Colony 14]]'s [[Homecoming Ceremony]], where 3 of his future enemies, [[Noah]], [[Eunie]], and [[Lanz]], as well as his future comrade [[Joran]] were in attendance.
[[File:Consul screenshot.png|thumb|left|With H, P, and O]] E is present at [[Origin]], during a discussion between all the Consuls on the results of the conflict in [[Alfeto Valley]] after [[D]] and Joran, now known as J, return to Origin. As [[O]] and [[P]] discuss the emergence of [[Ouroboros]], E joins them in discussion, when [[H]] interjects, insisting that she should be allowed to go eliminate them herself. He reminds her that she had already had fun recently, when she destroyed [[Colony 8]], insisting he be allowed to go himself. This discussion is interrupted by [[Z]], and ultimately [[K]] is chosen to eliminate Ouroboros, though he was unsuccessful.
Eventually, Ouroboros make their way to Colony Iota, where they encounter and defeat E, having been set up to do so by Alexandria, who had realized what the Consuls were up to with the intel she gathered. E attempts to fight Ouroboros, but is struck down.
== Personality == E, like most of his fellow Consuls, is arrogant and sociopathic. He demands to be addressed as "Master" E by both friend and foe alike. He views the world as a stage for a play and himself as a playwright. To him, everyone else, whether friend or foe, is a character for his work. In particular, he saw Alexandria as the perfect candidate to star in his masterpiece, planning to break her spirit and reforge her to his image. Unlike other Consuls, E does not appear to exert direct control over his subordinates. He instead gives them some leeway in the day-to-day operations and is amicable to negotiating additional resources for his assigned colony. However, he will also abandon a colony to destruction, as was the case with a Kevesi Colony he oversaw. At the moment of his death, E appeared to enter a state of delusion, imagining a crowd applauding a magnificent performance as a play closed. Alexandria mentions that he also had some shady hobbies and liked to talk. {{clr}}
